1
00:00:31,013 --> 00:00:32,596
[music]

2
00:01:33,073 --> 00:01:35,406
Big truck's
comin' up through here.

3
00:01:35,739 --> 00:01:38,654
Ah, it'd be a mess
of potholes come spring.

4
00:01:38,946 --> 00:01:41,362
Yeah.

5
00:01:43,237 --> 00:01:46,152
Is someone new
moving into town?

6
00:01:46,485 --> 00:01:48,901
Haven't heard anything yet.

7
00:02:00,106 --> 00:02:02,146
(male #1) I just want more hay.

8
00:02:02,396 --> 00:02:03,771
You what?

9
00:02:04,104 --> 00:02:05,436
I want more hay.

10
00:02:05,686 --> 00:02:06,603
Oh, who's this?

11
00:02:06,936 --> 00:02:09,852
Look at this.

12
00:02:10,144 --> 00:02:11,268
Whoa!

13
00:02:11,518 --> 00:02:13,142
Well, well, well, if it isn't
the Reed brothers.

14
00:02:13,392 --> 00:02:14,350
I've been looking for you boys.

15
00:02:14,684 --> 00:02:16,016
Do my eyes deceive me?

16
00:02:16,266 --> 00:02:18,183
(male #2) You know, I
heard you were mayor,

17
00:02:18,516 --> 00:02:19,806
but it turns out
you're the handyman.

18
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:22,472
Funny, you can't trust
a rumor mill, can you?

19
00:02:22,764 --> 00:02:25,138
Mitch Bright.

20
00:02:25,471 --> 00:02:28,678
Well, when you're
the mayor of a small town,

21
00:02:28,928 --> 00:02:31,677
you got to wear
a lot of different hats.

22
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:34,635
You building a new edition?

23
00:02:34,884 --> 00:02:36,468
You're funny.

24
00:02:36,717 --> 00:02:39,758
We're building a platform
for the town Christmas display.

25
00:02:40,091 --> 00:02:42,465
You might remember it, huh?

26
00:02:42,715 --> 00:02:45,131
I don't know, we just
Figured after Eve decades,

27
00:02:45,381 --> 00:02:48,505
the mother of God deserved
a proper place to kneel.

28
00:02:48,838 --> 00:02:49,671
It's only right.

29
00:02:50,005 --> 00:02:51,504
All the statues and everything?
Yeah, right.

30
00:02:51,837 --> 00:02:53,004
I remember that.

31
00:02:53,254 --> 00:02:54,503
So how you guys doing?

32
00:02:54,836 --> 00:02:56,419
Good.
Wow.

33
00:02:56,752 --> 00:02:58,334
How long has it been?

34
00:02:58,669 --> 00:03:00,584
I'm thinking.

35
00:03:01,751 --> 00:03:03,666
What brings you to town, Mitch?
Some hotshot attorney...

36
00:03:06,124 --> 00:03:07,374
Oh, he's loaded now.

37
00:03:07,665 --> 00:03:08,540
Who struck it rich.

38
00:03:08,789 --> 00:03:10,581
Yeah, I've made some
good investments, you know,

39
00:03:10,831 --> 00:03:12,455
but I miss the old town.

40
00:03:12,704 --> 00:03:15,453
Thought maybe I'd come back
and check out the old place,

41
00:03:15,703 --> 00:03:17,370
you know, see some
of my old friends.

42
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:19,994
Hey, how's Kristen doing?

43
00:03:20,285 --> 00:03:22,410
Here it comes.

44
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,367
She's good.

45
00:03:24,617 --> 00:03:26,616
Our kids are good too.
Mean anything by it.

46
00:03:28,824 --> 00:03:30,406
I... you know,
I was just being polite.

47
00:03:30,699 --> 00:03:33,364
Look, we're not in high school
anymore, Dan.

48
00:03:34,406 --> 00:03:35,655
Look, I got to run.

49
00:03:35,946 --> 00:03:38,029
I've got a big moving van
with all my stuff in it,

50
00:03:38,279 --> 00:03:39,987
gonna take a look
at the old house.

51
00:03:40,237 --> 00:03:41,486
I'm sure I'll be seeing
you boys around though.

52
00:03:41,778 --> 00:03:43,028
Oh, yes, you will.

53
00:03:43,319 --> 00:03:44,985
All right.

54
00:03:46,901 --> 00:03:48,443
Moving van?

55
00:03:48,692 --> 00:03:51,358
Isn't exactly a home
for the holidays.

56
00:03:51,608 --> 00:03:55,481
Hey, you want me to follow him?

57
00:04:01,687 --> 00:04:03,229
Pretty good, huh?

58
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:04,853
Not bad.

59
00:04:05,144 --> 00:04:06,270
Not a winning time, but...

60
00:04:06,519 --> 00:04:08,561
Want me to time you?

61
00:04:08,894 --> 00:04:10,434
No, I don't want
to hold you up.

62
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:12,101
I can wait.

63
00:04:12,351 --> 00:04:14,392
I'm just taking it easy today.

64
00:04:14,725 --> 00:04:16,016
Christmas Cup is coming up.

65
00:04:16,266 --> 00:04:17,724
You entering?
Of course.

66
00:04:17,974 --> 00:04:22,597
Me too.
Good luck.

67
00:04:30,636 --> 00:04:32,469
I'm gonna be the angel!

68
00:04:32,719 --> 00:04:34,342
You already are an angel.

69
00:04:34,592 --> 00:04:35,842
In the Christmas program, Dad.

70
00:04:36,175 --> 00:04:37,383
That means I get lines.

71
00:04:37,633 --> 00:04:39,424
Wow, lines.

72
00:04:39,674 --> 00:04:40,799
All the other kids
just have to sing,

73
00:04:41,132 --> 00:04:44,006
but I get to say stuff
too, and wear a costume.

74
00:04:44,298 --> 00:04:47,422
Oh, I am so glad you're home.

75
00:04:48,754 --> 00:04:50,421
Can you help set the table?

76
00:04:50,754 --> 00:04:55,877
I have people
who do that for me.

77
00:04:56,127 --> 00:04:57,418
What happened?

78
00:04:57,751 --> 00:04:58,876
What do you mean?

79
00:04:59,126 --> 00:05:00,958
You only joke about your lack
of actual power

80
00:05:01,209 --> 00:05:02,916
when you've had
a run-in at work.

81
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:04,624
Is that true?

82
00:05:06,664 --> 00:05:09,705
Hmm, well, nothing happened.

83
00:05:11,246 --> 00:05:12,913
Okay.

84
00:05:17,536 --> 00:05:21,326
Mitch Bright
stopped by town today.

85
00:05:21,577 --> 00:05:23,284
High school Mitch Bright?

86
00:05:23,534 --> 00:05:24,617
Mm-hmm.

87
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,574
Is he the rich guy?

88
00:05:28,449 --> 00:05:31,156
When I was waiting
for you at school,

89
00:05:31,406 --> 00:05:33,447
all the other teachers
were talking about it.

90
00:05:33,780 --> 00:05:36,405
Somebody saw him
in a big moving van.

91
00:05:36,738 --> 00:05:38,195
I thought you
were supposed to be

92
00:05:38,528 --> 00:05:39,862
your mother's
teacher assistant?

93
00:05:40,111 --> 00:05:41,444
She won't let me
grade the papers.

94
00:05:41,735 --> 00:05:42,860
Ooh.

95
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:44,234
So he had a big moving van?

96
00:05:44,568 --> 00:05:45,443
Mm-hmm.

97
00:05:45,734 --> 00:05:46,859
Hey, where's Cody?

98
00:05:47,108 --> 00:05:48,442
Cody, dinner's ready!

99
00:05:48,692 --> 00:05:50,775
He says he's home
for the holidays.

100
00:05:51,066 --> 00:05:53,606
Yeah, but his family
hasn't been here in years.

101
00:05:53,857 --> 00:05:56,105
Yeah, I know.

102
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:59,437
Seems highly suspect.

103
00:05:59,730 --> 00:06:02,186
Well, you think we should
invite him for dinner?

104
00:06:02,437 --> 00:06:04,519
Oh, no, I don't think we can
feed him in the manner to which

105
00:06:04,852 --> 00:06:05,977
he has become accustomed.

106
00:06:06,227 --> 00:06:07,560
Oh, come on.

107
00:06:09,434 --> 00:06:10,475
Yes, you do.

108
00:06:10,808 --> 00:06:13,308
Cody!
Oh, hi honey, sorry.

109
00:06:13,641 --> 00:06:14,599
Okay.

110
00:06:14,891 --> 00:06:17,307
All right.

111
00:06:19,514 --> 00:06:20,889
Hey, what's wrong with you?

112
00:06:21,139 --> 00:06:23,679
All the girls are reading
these vampire books.

113
00:06:24,595 --> 00:06:25,720
I don't get it.

114
00:06:26,012 --> 00:06:28,469
He wants the girls
to be in love with him instead.

115
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,468
Okay, all right.

116
00:06:30,718 --> 00:06:32,010
Listen, your mom
read all those books.

117
00:06:32,343 --> 00:06:33,634
I know exactly how you feel.

118
00:06:33,884 --> 00:06:37,425
Mm, can we please End
something to thank God for?

119
00:06:37,675 --> 00:06:39,798
Yes.
I get to be the angel.

120
00:06:40,131 --> 00:06:42,339
It's gonna be the best
Christmas ever.

121
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:46,963
[music]

122
00:06:59,042 --> 00:07:01,458
That was fast.

123
00:07:01,749 --> 00:07:03,207
Thanks for lettin' me drive.

124
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,873
Yeah.

125
00:07:05,165 --> 00:07:06,998
That's the last time.

126
00:07:20,659 --> 00:07:23,075
So who's that guy you were
talking about last night?

127
00:07:23,325 --> 00:07:24,325
Mitch Bright.

128
00:07:24,575 --> 00:07:27,490
Just a guy
from back in the day.

129
00:07:28,864 --> 00:07:31,655
We didn't get along
too well unfortunately.

130
00:07:31,947 --> 00:07:34,987
You had a high school rival?

131
00:07:35,237 --> 00:07:36,279
Yeah, why?

132
00:07:36,612 --> 00:07:39,028
What's so unusual about that?

133
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:42,194
Just seems like
everybody likes you.

134
00:07:42,527 --> 00:07:45,734
You need to go to some
city council meetings.

135
00:07:47,108 --> 00:07:48,816
So what did you
guys compete over?

136
00:07:49,149 --> 00:07:51,190
Oh, everything.

137
00:07:51,482 --> 00:07:56,188
Football, basketball, skiing,
running, class offices,

138
00:07:56,439 --> 00:08:00,354
parking spaces...mom.

139
00:08:00,603 --> 00:08:02,312
Mom?

140
00:08:02,561 --> 00:08:04,019
I won that one.

141
00:08:04,269 --> 00:08:05,269
Really?

142
00:08:05,519 --> 00:08:11,225
Your mom was
the girl in high school.

143
00:08:11,517 --> 00:08:14,391
Still is.

144
00:08:16,014 --> 00:08:18,722
Now you're lucky if you made
it this far without a rival,

145
00:08:18,972 --> 00:08:21,804
without someone to push you
and try to beat you

146
00:08:22,054 --> 00:08:23,887
at what you're good at.

147
00:08:24,137 --> 00:08:26,053
I didn't say that.

148
00:08:26,386 --> 00:08:27,594
Really?

149
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,759
Somebody's giving you trouble?

150
00:08:32,051 --> 00:08:36,299
My situation's a lot
different than yours.

151
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:38,424
Yours seems a lot easier.

152
00:08:38,673 --> 00:08:40,048
Of course.

153
00:08:40,298 --> 00:08:42,297
Of course yours is worse.

154
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:46,379
How is yours worse?

155
00:08:46,629 --> 00:08:49,004
Mine's a girl.

156
00:08:49,253 --> 00:08:51,085
Okay.

157
00:08:54,417 --> 00:08:55,959
Morning.

158
00:08:56,209 --> 00:08:57,917
Good morning.

159
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:00,749
Can I get a cafe American
with soy, please?

160
00:09:00,999 --> 00:09:02,581
Sure.

161
00:09:02,831 --> 00:09:06,038
Hey, now Josie, how's business?

162
00:09:06,372 --> 00:09:08,038
I can't complain.

163
00:09:08,371 --> 00:09:09,455
Customers are loyal.

164
00:09:09,704 --> 00:09:12,245
What do you think it
would take to make it better?

165
00:09:12,495 --> 00:09:14,619
More customers, I guess.

166
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:16,244
Exactly.

167
00:09:16,493 --> 00:09:18,701
You know, I have some ideas
on how I think

168
00:09:19,034 --> 00:09:20,200
I can make that happen.

169
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:21,825
You interested?

170
00:09:22,117 --> 00:09:23,241
Sure.

171
00:09:23,491 --> 00:09:24,366
Good.

172
00:09:24,657 --> 00:09:29,114
[whistling]

173
00:09:29,405 --> 00:09:33,862
Man, Christmas
is an awesome time of year,

174
00:09:34,112 --> 00:09:35,195
am I right?

175
00:09:35,529 --> 00:09:37,028
Hey, Santa.

176
00:09:37,319 --> 00:09:38,653
No, really.
I mean, think about it,

177
00:09:38,903 --> 00:09:40,651
this is the only time of year

178
00:09:40,901 --> 00:09:44,317
the entire world has this like
shared experience of peace

179
00:09:44,609 --> 00:09:49,273
and hope for the future and
strangers are loving each other.

180
00:09:49,523 --> 00:09:52,605
And there's that something
in the air, man, it's something.

181
00:09:52,897 --> 00:09:58,228
[singing]

182
00:09:59,937 --> 00:10:01,477
What is wrong with you?

183
00:10:01,811 --> 00:10:03,060
It's been a great week, man.

184
00:10:03,310 --> 00:10:04,226
Are you kidding me?

185
00:10:04,476 --> 00:10:08,101
We had two ice Fishermen
and the snow machine tool.

186
00:10:08,392 --> 00:10:15,098
Kristen invited Mitch to our
Christmas party Sunday night.

187
00:10:15,431 --> 00:10:18,222
She said it was
the Christian thing to do.

188
00:10:18,555 --> 00:10:20,929
Man, why does Kristen
always have to be right?

189
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:22,429
Yeah.

190
00:10:24,219 --> 00:10:27,010
I know he's got an angle.

191
00:10:27,343 --> 00:10:32,716
Now why would he come back
here after so many years?

192
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:36,465
What's he after?

193
00:10:36,715 --> 00:10:38,215
I don't know.

194
00:10:38,464 --> 00:10:40,922
Maybe he's just weary
of his city life

195
00:10:41,214 --> 00:10:44,254
and he wants to return
to the simple town of his youth.

196
00:10:44,546 --> 00:10:47,295
Or he's still mad at ya
after all the times you beat him

197
00:10:47,628 --> 00:10:49,128
in high school.

198
00:10:49,378 --> 00:10:51,335
And so after festering
for 20 years,

199
00:10:51,669 --> 00:10:53,959
he's returned
to exact his revenge.

200
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,916
[laughing]

201
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:58,707
Yeah, you know, could
you back to singing?

202
00:10:58,957 --> 00:11:01,165
Because you're
a lot less annoying.

203
00:11:01,498 --> 00:11:03,956
Thanks for the help.

204
00:11:04,289 --> 00:11:06,205
[singing]

205
00:11:08,537 --> 00:11:11,244
(Mitch Bright)
Well, it's getting late.

206
00:11:11,494 --> 00:11:15,119
You know I wasn't arguing
about your policies.

207
00:11:15,369 --> 00:11:17,785
It's... well, it's
more your approach.

208
00:11:18,118 --> 00:11:19,700
I don't know what you mean.

209
00:11:20,033 --> 00:11:21,741
I think the mistake that
you're making is assuming

210
00:11:22,033 --> 00:11:23,616
that you're every man.

211
00:11:23,949 --> 00:11:27,614
I Fund your ideals to be wildly
conservative compared

212
00:11:27,905 --> 00:11:29,905
to the rest of the country.

213
00:11:30,155 --> 00:11:32,070
This is coming from the guy
that went to Berkeley

214
00:11:32,321 --> 00:11:33,820
and lived in San Francisco
for 10 years,

215
00:11:34,070 --> 00:11:38,319
'cause when I think every man,
I think San Francisco.

216
00:11:40,193 --> 00:11:43,108
When's the last time
you left Alaska?

217
00:11:43,441 --> 00:11:44,525
I don't know, Mitch.

218
00:11:44,775 --> 00:11:46,565
I've been so busy building
bomb shelters

219
00:11:46,815 --> 00:11:49,148
and publishing
conspiracy papers

220
00:11:49,439 --> 00:11:51,189
that I haven't had time
to get out.

221
00:11:51,439 --> 00:11:53,813
Look, just 'cause we're
the 49th state doesn't make us

222
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:55,312
a third world.

223
00:11:55,562 --> 00:11:57,978
Look, there is a surprising
amount of hocus-pocus here.

224
00:11:58,269 --> 00:12:01,018
Oh, you mean... what,
Native religion?

225
00:12:01,268 --> 00:12:02,643
No, I mean Christianity.

226
00:12:02,976 --> 00:12:04,851
Well, it seems I recall you
competing with Dan

227
00:12:05,101 --> 00:12:07,309
for president of the youth group
back in the day.

228
00:12:07,642 --> 00:12:09,432
Well, there isn't much I
wouldn't compete with Dan about,

229
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:13,473
So, that was an act?

230
00:12:13,765 --> 00:12:14,889
No, not an act.

231
00:12:15,180 --> 00:12:18,138
Look, if you had an opportunity
to travel the world as I have,

232
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:20,345
you would know that
American culture is not limited

233
00:12:20,637 --> 00:12:23,136
to this small town bubble
that you live in.

234
00:12:23,469 --> 00:12:29,301
America is vast and diverse
and loving, peaceful, tolerant.

235
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:32,508
Yeah, no, I'm just... 
I'm trying to understand

236
00:12:32,757 --> 00:12:35,132
what you're implying.

237
00:12:35,382 --> 00:12:37,465
I would be willing to wager
that a majority of the people

238
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:41,296
in this town Find your
religious piety annoying.

239
00:12:41,588 --> 00:12:42,588
Annoying?

240
00:12:42,921 --> 00:12:44,045
Yes.

241
00:12:44,295 --> 00:12:46,128
And they reelect me because?

242
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:48,419
Well, you ran unopposed
in the last two elections, Dan.

243
00:12:48,752 --> 00:12:51,210
Because he's doing
such a good job.

244
00:12:51,543 --> 00:12:52,667
Yes.

245
00:12:52,917 --> 00:12:56,707
I'm sure he is
in a very small town way.

246
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:59,081
I don't agree with you, Mitch.

247
00:12:59,415 --> 00:13:01,123
Just because God's out of vogue
in the big city doesn't mean

248
00:13:01,456 --> 00:13:04,038
we throw him away like last
summer's fashion magazine.

249
00:13:04,371 --> 00:13:05,412
Maybe you wouldn't.

250
00:13:05,662 --> 00:13:07,287
Maybe a lot of your
close friends

251
00:13:07,537 --> 00:13:09,120
that were here tonight wouldn't.

252
00:13:09,412 --> 00:13:14,243
But I guess there's
no way to prove it, is there?

253
00:13:14,493 --> 00:13:19,366
You know, maybe I would
make a good mayor someday.

254
00:13:19,658 --> 00:13:20,866
You might.

255
00:13:21,157 --> 00:13:22,198
Yeah, I kinda like that.

256
00:13:22,490 --> 00:13:25,530
Mayor Mitch Bright.
Has a ring to it.

257
00:13:25,864 --> 00:13:26,989
Good night!

258
00:13:27,239 --> 00:13:29,197
Good night.

259
00:13:35,278 --> 00:13:36,527
Hey!

260
00:13:36,777 --> 00:13:38,526
Hey, sweetie.

261
00:13:38,776 --> 00:13:39,900
Can I come in?

262
00:13:40,234 --> 00:13:41,151
Yeah!

263
00:13:41,484 --> 00:13:43,441
I didn't know
if you're closed or...

264
00:13:43,692 --> 00:13:45,149
The second time in today.

265
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:47,273
I'm unforgettable.

266
00:13:48,106 --> 00:13:49,147
Coffee, black?

267
