I'm sorry, did you say,

781
00:38:32,917 --> 00:38:36,457
"The same boring, old program"?

782
00:38:39,873 --> 00:38:46,703
I am offended that you
could ever believe to End

783
00:38:47,036 --> 00:38:51,910
performers like Makayla
and myself could ever deliver.

784
00:38:56,284 --> 00:38:59,200
You're gonna change
the story, then?

785
00:38:59,449 --> 00:39:00,740
I don't have to change
the story.

786
00:39:01,032 --> 00:39:02,157
Don't you get it?

787
00:39:02,407 --> 00:39:05,156
The Christmas story is
the greatest story of all time.

788
00:39:05,406 --> 00:39:08,779
The Christmas story is
none like any other.

789
00:39:09,029 --> 00:39:11,403
It's got it all.
It's got intrigue.

790
00:39:11,695 --> 00:39:13,695
It's got scandal.
It's got surprise.

791
00:39:13,944 --> 00:39:16,610
So I'll tell you
what, Mr. know-it-all,

792
00:39:16,860 --> 00:39:19,567
why don't you two sit there,
hang on to your long johns,

793
00:39:19,817 --> 00:39:24,648
and observe the masters at work.

794
00:39:25,690 --> 00:39:28,065
[singing] Me, me,
me, me, me, me, me.

795
00:39:28,356 --> 00:39:29,730
[singing]
You, you, you, you, you.

796
00:39:30,063 --> 00:39:31,605
[laughing]

797
00:39:31,938 --> 00:39:33,562
Okay, action.

798
00:39:33,896 --> 00:39:38,102
In a world where there was no
television or Xbox or texting,

799
00:39:38,352 --> 00:39:42,267
one girl is about to experience
the greatest challenge

800
00:39:42,517 --> 00:39:43,684
of her life.

801
00:39:43,975 --> 00:39:46,724
Look at me, I'm just a girl
trying not to step anywhere

802
00:39:46,974 --> 00:39:48,265
onto scorpions 'cause I
have no socks to...

803
00:39:48,599 --> 00:39:49,765
Do not be afraid.

804
00:39:50,015 --> 00:39:52,056
[screaming]

805
00:39:52,389 --> 00:39:54,055
You have found favor with God.

806
00:39:54,389 --> 00:39:56,512
You will give birth to a child
and call his name Jesus.

807
00:39:56,762 --> 00:39:57,679
Is that right?

808
00:39:57,929 --> 00:39:59,345
Well, what in the world
would she say?

809
00:39:59,594 --> 00:40:01,594
Um, actually, I'm not really
good with this because

810
00:40:01,885 --> 00:40:05,093
you see, I'm suddenly, like,
pregnant without explanation,

811
00:40:05,384 --> 00:40:07,800
which means my fiance can try
to, like, oflicially stone me,

812
00:40:08,133 --> 00:40:09,716
which completely
ruins my makeup.

813
00:40:10,049 --> 00:40:12,465
And my BFFs will, like,
never speak to me again.

814
00:40:12,757 --> 00:40:15,298
So I really don't see
that as God's favorite.

815
00:40:15,548 --> 00:40:16,838
[laughing]

816
00:40:17,130 --> 00:40:18,380
She didn't say that.

817
00:40:18,713 --> 00:40:20,295
No, that's what everybody
today would have said.

818
00:40:20,545 --> 00:40:22,711
What she actually said was,

819
00:40:23,003 --> 00:40:27,127
"Let it be done to me
as thou hath said,"

820
00:40:27,377 --> 00:40:30,834
because it's really always
spoke with an English accent.

821
00:40:31,083 --> 00:40:33,583
Of course, if she did say
that, it was a little,

822
00:40:33,833 --> 00:40:39,414
little bit more like,
"Go ahead.

823
00:40:39,664 --> 00:40:41,580
Make my baby."

824
00:40:41,830 --> 00:40:43,079
[giggling]

825
00:40:43,371 --> 00:40:44,579
You don't have to stay.

826
00:40:44,871 --> 00:40:46,619
I'm good.

827
00:40:46,870 --> 00:40:48,036
Act two.

828
00:40:48,327 --> 00:40:49,493
Matter of fact,
we're missing somebody.

829
00:40:49,786 --> 00:40:52,617
I know, Joseph.

830
00:40:54,242 --> 00:40:56,158
Stand right here, perfectly.

831
00:40:56,408 --> 00:40:58,074
Try to look handsome for once.

832
00:40:59,449 --> 00:41:02,031
Anna, forgive me
for looking at this so simply.

833
00:41:02,281 --> 00:41:04,113
I teach elementary
kids after all,

834
00:41:04,364 --> 00:41:08,654
but Christmas starts
with a capital.

835
00:41:08,904 --> 00:41:11,902
The "C" comes
from a name, Christ.

836
00:41:12,194 --> 00:41:15,359
Christ the Lord is the center
of Christmas, not our rights,

837
00:41:15,651 --> 00:41:16,568
not our tradition.

838
00:41:16,818 --> 00:41:19,983
None of that matters if it
starts to detract us

839
00:41:20,316 --> 00:41:23,981
from the one whose birth
we celebrate, right?

840
00:41:24,314 --> 00:41:25,690
(Dan Reed) Right.

841
00:41:26,023 --> 00:41:28,314
And forgive me, Dan, but I
don't think this is something

842
00:41:28,564 --> 00:41:31,188
city hall can do.

843
00:41:31,438 --> 00:41:33,812
But it is something
that we as Christians can do,

844
00:41:34,103 --> 00:41:36,310
something we have to do.

845
00:41:36,603 --> 00:41:40,518
If we spent less time worrying
about our rights and more time

846
00:41:40,851 --> 00:41:42,600
worrying about others' needs,

847
00:41:42,892 --> 00:41:48,473
then I think we might
actually be doing Christmas.

848
00:41:50,763 --> 00:41:53,388
And once they arrive,
what happens?

849
00:41:53,679 --> 00:41:55,262
They meet up with crazy people.

850
00:41:55,554 --> 00:41:57,637
Joe, what do you twos want?

851
00:41:57,887 --> 00:41:59,760
Well, like the hundreds
of other people here,

852
00:42:00,053 --> 00:42:01,718
WE want a room.

853
00:42:01,968 --> 00:42:06,550
Please, I'm having
a baby right now!

854
00:42:06,842 --> 00:42:08,424
Yeah, like I
haven't heard that.

855
00:42:08,675 --> 00:42:12,132
I'll tell you what, you
twos can go into the barn.

856
00:42:12,381 --> 00:42:13,922
And they do.

857
00:42:14,172 --> 00:42:19,545
Mary is rushed
off to have her baby,

858
00:42:19,878 --> 00:42:22,128
but she does it offstage
since it's kind of icky.

859
00:42:22,419 --> 00:42:25,585
And she possibly did it alone
because it would've made Joseph

860
00:42:25,876 --> 00:42:30,458
ceremonially unclean, which
makes Mary not only a saint,

861
00:42:30,750 --> 00:42:34,498
but he's kind of reachin'
action figuree status in my book.

862
00:42:34,748 --> 00:42:35,915
Come here.

863
00:42:36,248 --> 00:42:37,372
[whispering]

864
00:42:37,622 --> 00:42:39,705
Cynical audience is
getting out of hand.

865
00:42:39,955 --> 00:42:41,704
Let's show 'em.
Come on.

866
00:42:41,954 --> 00:42:43,912
[whistling]

867
00:42:44,245 --> 00:42:45,578
[gasping]

868
00:42:45,869 --> 00:42:52,784
Look, God of the universe
decides to enter our domain

869
00:42:53,076 --> 00:42:56,574
in the most fragile form.

870
00:42:56,907 --> 00:42:58,073
Can I have him?

871
00:42:58,324 --> 00:42:59,656
There's the baby.

872
00:42:59,948 --> 00:43:00,905
Aw.

873
00:43:01,156 --> 00:43:03,280
That a human can take.

874
00:43:03,613 --> 00:43:05,696
Wow.

875
00:43:07,779 --> 00:43:11,943
Here, I'm gonna let you
be Mary for a little bit.

876
00:43:12,235 --> 00:43:15,275
(Reverend Tiller) When God, the Father,
sent his Son to redeem the earth

877
00:43:15,567 --> 00:43:16,692
it was a gift.

878
00:43:16,984 --> 00:43:19,025
Some people welcomed it
with great joy,

879
00:43:19,358 --> 00:43:20,982
others spit upon it.

880
00:43:21,315 --> 00:43:25,647
Two thousand years later,
nothing has changed.

881
00:43:25,980 --> 00:43:30,771
We give the gift with love, with humility, and with grace.
To that gift is not our concern.

882
00:43:34,644 --> 00:43:38,351
How we respond
to the people is God's concern.

883
00:43:38,684 --> 00:43:40,808
(Dan Reed) Are we supposed to
just let people like Mitch.

884
00:43:42,850 --> 00:43:46,057
No, we're not saying
we roll over.

885
00:43:46,348 --> 00:43:50,555
We just prove him wrong
by action, not argument.

886
00:43:50,805 --> 00:43:53,553
I don't know what that means.

887
00:43:53,804 --> 00:43:55,720
I don't either.

888
00:43:55,969 --> 00:43:59,511
However, what does this
Christmas with a capital 'C'

889
00:43:59,761 --> 00:44:01,259
look like?

890
00:44:01,509 --> 00:44:03,592
Like Philippians 2.

891
00:44:03,884 --> 00:44:06,466
Jesus did not consider equality
with God

892
00:44:06,758 --> 00:44:08,507
something that could be grasped.

893
00:44:08,799 --> 00:44:10,756
He made himself nothing.
On the very nature of a servant.

894
00:44:16,879 --> 00:44:19,628
Hmm.

895
00:44:19,919 --> 00:44:23,502
(Greg Reed) The people
expected a political Messiah.

896
00:44:25,251 --> 00:44:27,500
Bet they didn't have
popcorn back then.

897
00:44:27,792 --> 00:44:29,625
But what did they get?

898
00:44:29,875 --> 00:44:35,290
God, instead of coming
down... shh, angels don't laugh.

899
00:44:35,581 --> 00:44:41,745
Instead of God coming down miraculously...
he humbled himself

900
00:44:46,411 --> 00:44:52,742
and he became God with us.

901
00:44:53,866 --> 00:44:58,781
And he began to heal humanity
by loving them.

902
00:45:04,654 --> 00:45:05,987
The end.

903
00:45:06,236 --> 00:45:07,570
Take your bow, son.

904
00:45:07,820 --> 00:45:12,276
And so, Makayla,
playing the angel.

905
00:45:12,568 --> 00:45:15,025
Joseph,
pathetically playing Joseph,

906
00:45:15,358 --> 00:45:17,149
and me as the donkey.

907
00:45:17,441 --> 00:45:18,649
Thank you.

908
00:45:18,899 --> 00:45:20,148
Take your bows.
Take your bows.

909
00:45:20,440 --> 00:45:21,690
You were wonderful, angel.

910
00:45:22,023 --> 00:45:24,606
And you were wonderful... no.

911
00:45:31,686 --> 00:45:34,477
So how's your knee?

912
00:45:34,810 --> 00:45:36,435
It's okay.

913
00:45:36,768 --> 00:45:39,559
You have to swear you
won't tell anybody about this,

914
00:45:39,850 --> 00:45:41,850
you know, at school.

915
00:45:42,099 --> 00:45:43,765
What?
The play?

916
00:45:45,015 --> 00:45:46,930
I'm serious.

917
00:45:48,555 --> 00:45:49,971
I'll make you a deal.

918
00:45:50,221 --> 00:45:53,303
I don't tell anyone at school,
you race the Christmas Cup.

919
00:45:53,595 --> 00:45:55,719
It's a deal.

920
00:45:59,260 --> 00:46:01,800
Sienna.

921
00:46:02,134 --> 00:46:03,633
Is that why you came out here?

922
00:46:03,966 --> 00:46:05,550
Make me race?

923
00:46:05,799 --> 00:46:10,547
No, I came to see
the Christmas show.

924
00:46:13,796 --> 00:46:15,379
Up a bit.

925
00:46:15,712 --> 00:46:17,212
I got to go down.

926
00:46:17,504 --> 00:46:19,211
Isaac, you're on.

927
00:46:19,544 --> 00:46:22,627
Can you get this?

928
00:46:23,834 --> 00:46:26,292
It looks so good,
you guys, I love it!

929
00:46:26,625 --> 00:46:28,207
All right!

930
00:46:34,623 --> 00:46:37,622
I guess anybody can hang
a banner these days.

931
00:46:38,621 --> 00:46:39,703
[knocking]

932
00:46:42,661 --> 00:46:45,160
Merry Christmas.

933
00:46:47,909 --> 00:46:50,117
(Josie) Who wants to buy an
angel for a kid whose parents

934
00:46:50,367 --> 00:46:52,783
are in prison?

935
00:46:58,697 --> 00:47:01,072
All right, that's good.

936
00:47:02,737 --> 00:47:05,236
Missed a spot.

937
00:47:07,111 --> 00:47:08,485
No, I didn't.

938
00:47:08,735 --> 00:47:09,860
Yeah, you did.

939
00:47:10,152 --> 00:47:11,817
Did I?

940
00:47:14,608 --> 00:47:16,025
Hot chocolate!

941
00:47:16,358 --> 00:47:18,732
Complementary hot chocolate
with a capital 'C.'

942
00:47:19,065 --> 00:47:20,564
I could give you
a shot of whipped cream.

943
00:47:20,814 --> 00:47:23,605
(female #3) I don't
know about that.

944
00:47:25,729 --> 00:47:26,896
Hi, Josie.

945
00:47:27,187 --> 00:47:28,895
Hi.

946
00:47:29,186 --> 00:47:30,936
Oh, last time I was in here,
I kind of accidentally

947
00:47:31,186 --> 00:47:33,352
stepped on your chair
with my muddy boots

948
00:47:33,685 --> 00:47:35,017
and made a big scene.

949
00:47:35,267 --> 00:47:36,726
I remember.

950
00:47:36,975 --> 00:47:38,850
Sorry.

951
00:47:40,724 --> 00:47:43,639
Came here to make it up to you.

952
00:47:52,220 --> 00:47:55,385
I'm good.

953
00:48:02,633 --> 00:48:04,382
You were way faster
the day we raced.

954
00:48:04,673 --> 00:48:06,881
The deal is that
I enter the Cup.

955
00:48:07,173 --> 00:48:08,964
I don't have to win it.

956
00:48:09,214 --> 00:48:11,089
With that attitude you won't.

957
00:48:11,338 --> 00:48:13,546
Thanks, Coach.

958
00:48:18,086 --> 00:48:20,419
(Kristen Reed) Whoa, whoa.

959
00:48:20,752 --> 00:48:22,167
Wow, looks like you
could use some help.

960
00:48:22,501 --> 00:48:23,584
What you doing?

961
00:48:23,834 --> 00:48:25,251
I have a really good idea.

962
00:48:25,584 --> 00:48:26,458
I want to make cookies

963
00:48:26,708 --> 00:48:28,458
for the Christmas
with a capital 'C' mission.

964
00:48:28,707 --> 00:48:30,456
Ah, that is a great idea.

965
00:48:30,706 --> 00:48:32,539
How about if I help you?

966
00:48:32,789 --> 00:48:33,705
There we go.

967
00:48:33,997 --> 00:48:35,580
I'll need your
help to deliver them.

968
00:48:35,829 --> 00:48:36,704
Can you drive me?

969
00:48:36,996 --> 00:48:38,162
Yeah, sure.

970
00:48:38,412 --> 00:48:39,536
Who are they for?

971
00:48:39,829 --> 00:48:41,869
Mitch Bright.

972
00:48:43,744 --> 00:48:45,243
Everybody's been doing
nice things

973
00:48:45,492 --> 00:48:47,325
for everybody all over town,

974
00:48:47,575 --> 00:48:51,949
but nobody's done anything
for him as far as I can tell.

975
00:48:52,199 --> 00:48:54,698
Well, maybe they just figure
he really doesn't need

976
00:48:54,990 --> 00:48:57,406
any help or want it.

977
00:48:57,739 --> 00:49:01,487
But everybody wants cookies.

978
00:49:09,568 --> 00:49:10,526
Come on, Mom!

979
00:49:10,776 --> 00:49:12,192
Why are you waiting?

980
00:49:12,484 --> 00:49:13,400
You go on ahead, angel.

981
00:49:13,650 --> 00:49:15,524
I'll just wait
for you here, okay?

982
00:49:25,728 --> 00:49:27,936
[knocking]

983
00:49:32,477 --> 00:49:35,392
I guess he's not home.

984
00:49:38,558 --> 00:49:40,473
Makayla.

985
00:49:59,675 --> 00:50:02,258
Hey, the important thing
is that you did it, right?

986
00:50:02,508 --> 00:50:06,214
He was supposed to know
he's a blessing from heaven.

987
00:50:06,464 --> 00:50:07,465
Do you think he'll get it?

988
00:50:07,798 --> 00:50:09,297
Sure, honey.

989
00:50:09,546 --> 00:50:15,336
Hey, he'll take one bite
and of course he'll know, okay?

990
00:50:33,705 --> 00:50:36,204
[laughing] I know.

991
00:50:36,453 --> 00:50:38,037
Where have you been?

992
00:50:38,328 --> 00:50:41,369
Honestly, I have been
trying to call you forever.

993
00:50:41,660 --> 00:50:43,701
Oh, we just went
out on a little mission, huh?

994
00:50:44,034 --> 00:50:45,451
Everything okay?

995
00:50:45,743 --> 00:50:49,116
The judge is coming tomorrow.

996
00:50:49,366 --> 00:50:50,948
Is that good or bad?

997
00:50:51,199 --> 00:50:52,656
I don't know.

998
00:50:52,948 --> 00:50:55,780
By the way, good.

999
00:50:56,030 --> 00:50:58,529
Ah, told ya.

1000
00:51:05,651 --> 00:51:08,400
How many Christmas cookies
did you have tonight?

1001
00:51:08,650 --> 00:51:10,442
Only about seven.

1002
00:51:10,692 --> 00:51:13,441
All right, let's
get you in bed, kiddo.

1003
00:51:13,690 --> 00:51:16,190
Come on.

1004
00:51:16,440 --> 00:51:19,438
That's it.
That's it.

1005
00:51:21,313 --> 00:51:22,687
What?

1006
00:51:23,020 --> 00:51:26,978
Mitch, he would never win.

1007
00:51:27,228 --> 00:51:28,477
Why do you say that?

1008
00:51:28,810 --> 00:51:31,351
Because he makes people grumpy.

1009
00:51:31,684 --> 00:51:37,557
I think he makes people
because he's grumpy.

1010
00:51:37,848 --> 00:51:40,139
Why though?

1011
00:51:40,473 --> 00:51:42,264
I don't know why.

1012
00:51:42,597 --> 00:51:46,179
That's a good question.

1013
00:51:48,595 --> 00:51:49,762
Let's pray, okay?

1014
00:51:50,053 --> 00:51:51,594
I guess we should pray for him.

1015
00:51:51,844 --> 00:51:53,427
Right.

1016
00:51:53,677 --> 00:51:54,843
Why don't you start?

1017
00:51:55,176 --> 00:51:58,091
Okay.

1018
00:51:58,342 --> 00:52:01,383
Dear Lord,
thank you for this day.

1019
00:52:01,633 --> 00:52:04,465
Please be with Mitch
and make him nice.

1020
00:52:04,798 --> 00:52:07,381
And let Daddy stay as Mayor.

1021
00:52:07,630 --> 00:52:10,296
In Jesus' name, amen.

1022
00:52:10,588 --> 00:52:12,670
Amen.

1023
00:52:12,962 --> 00:52:14,628
All right.

1024
00:52:16,710 --> 00:52:17,668
Night.

1025
00:52:17,918 --> 00:52:19,793
Night, I love you.

1026
00:52:20,792 --> 00:52:24,958
(female #4) Perhaps you all can
show me what will be placed here.

1027
00:52:25,291 --> 00:52:29,206
Well, there they are.

1028
00:52:29,497 --> 00:52:31,913
Can you bring
them out a little?

1029
00:52:32,246 --> 00:52:33,663
Yeah, sure.

1030
00:52:35,079 --> 00:52:37,703
Okay.

1031
00:52:40,077 --> 00:52:42,535
There she is.

1032
00:52:42,868 --> 00:52:45,409
They're beautiful.

1033
00:52:45,700 --> 00:52:46,658
Someone made these?

1034
00:52:46,991 --> 00:52:48,991
(Dan Reed) Over 50 years ago.

1035
00:52:49,240 --> 00:52:52,156
They were carved by a man
who worked in a lumber mill

1036
00:52:52,448 --> 00:52:54,614
and donated to the town.

1037
00:52:54,905 --> 00:52:57,196
Are there any other
elements to the display?

1038
00:52:57,529 --> 00:52:58,737
Oh, yeah.

1039
00:52:58,987 --> 00:53:02,277
Some animals, a couple
sheep, and a donkey.

1040
00:53:02,611 --> 00:53:04,735
Well, let's have
a talk, shall we?

1041
00:53:07,109 --> 00:53:09,442
I assume you've studied
the case law related

1042
00:53:09,692 --> 00:53:12,024
to the establishment clause?

1043
00:53:12,357 --> 00:53:14,065
We have.

1044
00:53:14,357 --> 00:53:18,105
She's been all over it
with a fine-toothed comb.

1045
00:53:18,355 --> 00:53:22,353
Well, on the record, I have
to tell you that if the creche

1046
00:53:22,645 --> 00:53:25,394
is the only element
of the holiday display

1047
00:53:25,685 --> 00:53:28,018
and it is owned
by the local government

1048
00:53:28,268 --> 00:53:30,517
and displayed
on government property...

1049
00:53:30,851 --> 00:53:33,808
Then you must rule against it.

1050
00:53:34,058 --> 00:53:36,182
Yes.

1051
00:53:36,515 --> 00:53:39,306
Off the record, I'll tell you
that I don't personally

1052
00:53:39,639 --> 00:53:42,471
want to make a ruling
against Jesus and Mary,

1053
00:53:42,721 --> 00:53:45,345
especially at Christmastime.

1054
00:53:45,637 --> 00:53:47,387
Thank God.

1055
00:53:48,178 --> 00:53:51,260
So, what are you saying?

1056
00:53:51,510 --> 00:53:55,301
Well, there are
three options to consider.

1057
00:53:55,551 --> 00:53:59,091
I mean, you could add to this
as a holiday display and include

1058
00:53:59,341 --> 00:54:01,757
elements of a nonreligious
nature or elements

1059
00:54:02,090 --> 00:54:04,631
that are of other faiths.

1060
00:54:04,964 --> 00:54:08,254
Or the city can donate
or sell them,

1061
00:54:08,546 --> 00:54:12,128
the statues and the platform,
to a private individual

1062
00:54:12,419 --> 00:54:14,585
who can display them
in another place,

1063
00:54:14,877 --> 00:54:17,084
either on private property

1064
00:54:17,418 --> 00:54:19,500
or with permission
in a public setting

1065
00:54:19,750 --> 00:54:21,458
where there is
equal opportunity for others

1066
00:54:21,708 --> 00:54:23,624
to put up their own
holiday displays.

1067
00:54:23,873 --> 00:54:25,332
And the third?

1068
00:54:25,623 --> 00:54:27,039
Don't display them at all.

1069
00:54:27,373 --> 00:54:30,247
But if you ask me,
that would be a shame.

1070
00:54:30,497 --> 00:54:32,412
With all due respect,
your Honor,

1071
00:54:32,662 --> 00:54:34,620
all three of those are ruining
our town's traditions

1072
00:54:34,911 --> 00:54:36,786
that we've had over 50 years.

1073
00:54:37,119 --> 00:54:40,160
Or you could look at it
as creating a new tradition.

1074
00:54:40,410 --> 00:54:44,533
I mean, moving the Christ child
to another place of honor.

1075
00:54:49,864 --> 00:54:53,446
Perhaps you are more
concerned about yours.

1076
00:54:53,780 --> 00:54:55,904
And this is
my advice on the case,

1077
00:54:56,154 --> 00:54:58,570
if you want to push for an official
ruling, will have to come down.

1078
00:55:00,902 --> 00:55:03,735
Otherwise, let me know what
you choose to do, okay?

1079
00:55:03,985 --> 00:55:05,235
Thank you, your Honor.

1080
00:55:05,526 --> 00:55:06,525
Yes, thank you.

1081
00:55:06,775 --> 00:55:07,899
Thank you, your Honor.

1082
00:55:08,234 --> 00:55:09,733
Merry Christmas.

1083
00:55:11,482 --> 00:55:13,439
(Dan Reed) Merry Christmas.

1084
00:55:14,565 --> 00:55:16,480
Big cruise ships
comin' up through here,

1085
00:55:16,771 --> 00:55:18,479
people tramplin' all over.

1086
00:55:18,771 --> 00:55:19,979
You know,
he says it's gonna bring

1087
00:55:20,229 --> 00:55:21,895
a bunch of money into town.

1088
00:55:22,186 --> 00:55:24,186
'Cause Alaska cruises,
you know, they got a lot

1089
00:55:24,436 --> 00:55:26,477
of retired people, you know,
old people, you know,

1090
00:55:26,810 --> 00:55:31,350
goin' on those shoestring budget
transportation tours together.

1091
00:55:31,684 --> 00:55:34,391
Bunch of old, widowed ladies.

1092
00:55:36,515 --> 00:55:39,555
Old, widowed ladies?

1093
00:55:40,472 --> 00:55:42,304
You got another one of those?

1094
00:55:42,596 --> 00:55:45,720
[laughing]

1095
00:55:51,634 --> 00:55:53,134
Coach.

1096
00:55:53,384 --> 00:55:54,383
Mayor.

1097
00:55:54,675 --> 00:55:56,758
Wow, nice button.

1098
00:55:57,091 --> 00:55:58,549
He's gonna bring
the cruise line order

1099
00:55:58,882 --> 00:56:00,214
to the race on Saturday.

1100
00:56:00,464 --> 00:56:01,340
Isn't that great?

1101
00:56:01,631 --> 00:56:03,756
Yeah, that's great.

1102
00:56:04,047 --> 00:56:06,087
See you inside, Coach.

1103
00:56:06,379 --> 00:56:09,086
You know, I can help you
tear this thing down.

1104
00:56:10,753 --> 00:56:12,586
I don't believe you would
actually help me

1105
00:56:12,877 --> 00:56:14,668
even if I planned
on takin' it down.

1106
00:56:14,918 --> 00:56:16,917
Oh, I could hire somebody.

1107
00:56:17,167 --> 00:56:18,667
It's not goin' anywhere.

1108
00:56:18,917 --> 00:56:20,832
Now you heard what
the judge said, Dan.

1109
00:56:21,125 --> 00:56:25,747
There's nothin' religious
about a bunch of planks of wood.

1110
00:56:26,039 --> 00:56:27,539
Look, if you want
to let it sit here empty,

1111
00:56:27,789 --> 00:56:29,163
that's fine with me.

1112
00:56:29,454 --> 00:56:31,121
I told you that you
were in the minority,

1113
00:56:31,412 --> 00:56:32,578
but you wouldn't listen.

1114
00:56:32,871 --> 00:56:35,535
Guess we'll Fund out come
spring election, huh?

1115
00:57:12,731 --> 00:57:14,272
(Kristen Reed) I got cocoa.

1116
00:57:14,522 --> 00:57:15,938
Mom, look at how long mine is.

1117
00:57:16,229 --> 00:57:18,229
No, no, no, no no!

1118
00:57:18,479 --> 00:57:22,310
You always get the railroads,
and I want to be the tycoon.

1119
00:57:22,603 --> 00:57:27,059
Why don't you send some
more marshmallows our way, huh?

1120
00:57:28,183 --> 00:57:31,516
(Greg Reed) Danny boy,
wife's talking to ya.

1121
00:57:32,932 --> 00:57:35,265
(Cody Reed) He's still
mad 'cause he lost.

1122
00:57:35,598 --> 00:57:37,223
Hey, hey, let's
do a midnight run.

1123
00:57:37,556 --> 00:57:39,972
Me, you, and Cody,
we'll take the nativity,

1124
00:57:40,305 --> 00:57:41,388
we'll stick it in the church.

1125
00:57:41,637 --> 00:57:43,887
No, no, no, let's
take it to the park.

1126
00:57:44,220 --> 00:57:45,427
That'd make you happy.

1127
00:57:45,677 --> 00:57:47,427
The Grinch ruined Christmas.

1128
00:57:47,677 --> 00:57:49,135
It doesn't make you mad?

1129
00:57:49,427 --> 00:57:51,300
(Kristen Reed)
He didn't ruin my Christmas.

1130
00:57:51,551 --> 00:57:53,300
Mine's okay.

1131
00:57:53,550 --> 00:57:55,258
(Makayla Reed) I mean, I'd
be a little grinchy too

1132
00:57:55,508 --> 00:57:56,799
if all I had in my house

1133
00:57:57,132 --> 00:57:59,131
was a little couch
and a suitcase.

1134
00:57:59,381 --> 00:58:01,048
What do you mean?

1135
00:58:01,297 --> 00:58:02,297
Yeah.

1136
00:58:02,588 --> 00:58:06,462
We're still talking about Mitch Bright, right?
You talking about?

1137
00:58:08,586 --> 00:58:10,086
Remember when we
delivered the cookies?

1138
00:58:10,377 --> 00:58:11,418
Well, when I looked
in the window,

1139
00:58:11,751 --> 00:58:14,334
all I saw was a little couch
and a suitcase.

1140
00:58:14,667 --> 00:58:18,875
Wait a minute,
in that whole big house?

1141
00:58:19,124 --> 00:58:23,081
What about his
grandmother's antiques?

1142
00:58:23,414 --> 00:58:25,289
And the moving van?

1143
00:58:25,539 --> 00:58:26,664
Wait a minute.

1144
00:58:26,955 --> 00:58:30,454
Are you tellin' me that the van
was taking antiques

1145
00:58:30,704 --> 00:58:32,369
away from his house?

1146
00:58:32,620 --> 00:58:34,743
Hang on, hang on,
let me try to figure this out.

1147
00:58:35,077 --> 00:58:36,701
I knew something was wrong.

1148
00:58:37,035 --> 00:58:41,116
Okay, so Mitch Bright
comes to town,

1149
00:58:41,367 --> 00:58:43,532
he sells or loses
everything he has.

1150
00:58:43,865 --> 00:58:47,157
He puts on this big show about
how rich, how successful he is,

1151
00:58:47,448 --> 00:58:48,572
how he's gonna save the town.

1152
00:58:48,864 --> 00:58:50,114
He's gonna run for mayor.

1153
00:58:50,405 --> 00:58:53,862
He puts the whole town
on edge over Christmas.

1154
00:58:54,154 --> 00:58:56,237
(Cody Reed)
Now that really makes sense.

1155
00:58:56,570 --> 00:59:00,734
I think this makes for a very
interesting story, don't you?

1156
00:59:00,984 --> 00:59:02,318
But what is it?

1157
00:59:02,568 --> 00:59:04,734
(Kristen Reed) Well maybe
it's none of our business.

1158
00:59:04,984 --> 00:59:06,233
Who wants more popcorn?

1159
00:59:06,482 --> 00:59:07,398
(Makayla Reed) Me!

1160
00:59:07,649 --> 00:59:08,898
Cody ate all mine.

1161
00:59:09,232 --> 00:59:10,565
You know what this
means, don't you?

1162
00:59:10,856 --> 00:59:12,189
Road trip.

1163
00:59:12,439 --> 00:59:13,356
Oh, I know that look.

1164
00:59:13,606 --> 00:59:16,355
You Reed brothers
are scheming again.

1165
00:59:16,604 --> 00:59:17,812
You know what, honey?

1166
00:59:18,103 --> 00:59:19,562
Greg and I are gonna pay
a little visit

1167
00:59:19,895 --> 00:59:21,227
to Mitch Brights law Hrm.

1168
00:59:21,519 --> 00:59:22,727
I'm gonna call Harland.

1169
00:59:23,019 --> 00:59:24,143
I'll have him get
the plane ready.

1170
00:59:24,393 --> 00:59:25,726
All right.

1171
00:59:25,976 --> 00:59:29,350
Your roll, Donald Trump.

1172
00:59:38,763 --> 00:59:42,095
Now, I mean, would it kill
you to let me be left seat once?

1173
00:59:42,428 --> 00:59:44,469
It might.
And we show up to this of lice,

1174
00:59:47,884 --> 00:59:49,176
you let me do the talking.

1175
00:59:49,426 --> 00:59:50,842
You sure this is a good idea?

1176
00:59:51,175 --> 00:59:52,675
'Cause I'm usually
game for anything.

1177
00:59:53,008 --> 00:59:54,132
I know.

1178
00:59:54,383 --> 00:59:56,673
I hope so.

1179
00:59:57,006 --> 00:59:59,422
I gotta take a wiz.

1180
01:00:03,546 --> 01:00:05,128
You're friends of Mitch Bright?

1181
01:00:05,420 --> 01:00:07,295
We went to high school
with him.

1182
01:00:07,628 --> 01:00:08,752
We're in town.

1183
01:00:09,003 --> 01:00:10,293
Thought we'd
stop by and say hey.

1184
01:00:10,627 --> 01:00:11,793
Well, sorry
to keep you waiting.

1185
01:00:12,043 --> 01:00:13,792
He doesn't work here anymore.

1186
01:00:14,042 --> 01:00:15,833
Oh.

1187
01:00:16,083 --> 01:00:19,040
Well, maybe you could tell us
what Hrm he went to or give us

1188
01:00:19,373 --> 01:00:20,582
an address where we
could look him up?

1189
01:00:20,832 --> 01:00:22,206
No.

1190
01:00:22,497 --> 01:00:23,664
No.

1191
01:00:25,455 --> 01:00:29,204
What, is it cloak and dagger
or is he big trouble?

1192
01:00:29,454 --> 01:00:31,577
No, sorry, the Firm's
just protective.

1193
01:00:33,993 --> 01:00:37,200
Mitch was never
anything but nice to me.

1194
01:00:37,450 --> 01:00:39,283
He gave me a shot
at a few cases a while back

1195
01:00:39,533 --> 01:00:42,366
and he helped me
get on good track here.

1196
01:00:43,781 --> 01:00:45,864
And all I know is is that he
ended up investing in something

1197
01:00:46,114 --> 01:00:49,404
he shouldn't have.

1198
01:00:49,738 --> 01:00:52,821
It went south.

1199
01:00:54,778 --> 01:00:59,651
He ended up losing everything,
including his job here.

1200
01:01:01,734 --> 01:01:04,191
Then, of course, nobody
ever talks about it.

1201
01:01:04,483 --> 01:01:05,982
I don't know where he went

1202
01:01:06,315 --> 01:01:08,065
or if he has any family
or friends to go to.

1203
01:01:08,356 --> 01:01:13,522
Well, his family's gone,
but he has... you know,

1204
01:01:13,813 --> 01:01:15,312
he has friends.

1205
01:01:15,562 --> 01:01:17,312
Like you guys?

1206
01:01:17,603 --> 01:01:18,769
Yeah.

1207
01:01:19,061 --> 01:01:20,935
Yeah, right.

1208
01:01:21,185 --> 01:01:25,226
When you see him,
you give him this.

1209
01:01:25,517 --> 01:01:28,974
Just tell him it's from an old
friend or do it anonymously.

1210
01:01:29,224 --> 01:01:30,974
I don't think that we could...

1211
01:01:31,224 --> 01:01:33,431
No, please.
To take it, but he needs it.

1212
01:01:37,638 --> 01:01:40,512
He really helped me
out a lot back then.

1213
01:01:40,762 --> 01:01:44,135
I just want to help him.

1214
01:01:45,177 --> 01:01:48,218
Well, that's all I know,
so I better get back to work.

1215
01:01:48,468 --> 01:01:49,592
Good luck to both of you.

1216
01:01:49,883 --> 01:01:51,758
Yeah, thanks for...

1217
01:01:52,091 --> 01:01:54,007
Good luck and Merry Christmas.

1218
01:01:54,257 --> 01:01:57,339
Merry Christmas to you.

1219
01:02:00,755 --> 01:02:05,169
So he's ruined, he comes
back to town hiding the fact.

1220
01:02:05,461 --> 01:02:07,752
What do you think
he's trying to do?

1221
01:02:08,002 --> 01:02:09,793
Get a life back.

1222
01:02:10,043 --> 01:02:11,959
Not a very good strategy
to run for mayor

1223
01:02:12,209 --> 01:02:13,833
while lying to everybody.

1224
01:02:14,083 --> 01:02:15,458
Yeah.

1225
01:02:15,708 --> 01:02:18,415
You know, I think this
whole cruise line thing

1226
01:02:18,665 --> 01:02:21,414
is just to get back in the game.

1227
01:02:21,664 --> 01:02:26,413
Maybe people will forgive him
when they End out the truth.

1228
01:02:27,370 --> 01:02:29,661
Or we could run him
out of here on a rail.

1229
01:02:29,994 --> 01:02:32,744
Yeah, that'd show him
the real spirit of Christmas.

1230
01:02:33,077 --> 01:02:34,242
It'd sure feel good.

1231
01:02:34,492 --> 01:02:36,325
Yeah.

1232
01:02:37,867 --> 01:02:39,158
Hey, Dad.

1233
01:02:39,408 --> 01:02:40,407
Hey, pal.
What's up?

1234
01:02:40,741 --> 01:02:42,240
Can you help me with these?

1235
01:02:42,531 --> 01:02:43,532
Sure.

1236
01:02:43,865 --> 01:02:46,155
Sure.
See you guys.

1237
01:02:46,447 --> 01:02:47,363
See you.

1238
01:02:47,696 --> 01:02:50,279
Ah, grab this thing, will you?

1239
01:02:51,820 --> 01:02:53,236
What's up, man?

1240
01:02:53,569 --> 01:02:56,194
You know that girl
I was telling you about?

1241
01:02:56,527 --> 01:02:59,026
Uh, not sure.

1242
01:03:00,358 --> 01:03:02,316
You know, she's
always trying to beat me.

1243
01:03:02,566 --> 01:03:03,690
We talked about it.

1244
01:03:03,983 --> 01:03:05,149
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1245
01:03:05,399 --> 01:03:06,731
What happened?

1246
01:03:07,065 --> 01:03:10,730
Well, see, we were racing.

1247
01:03:11,063 --> 01:03:12,187
Yeah.

1248
01:03:12,437 --> 01:03:16,770
She was winning,
but then she fell and hurt.

1249
01:03:17,061 --> 01:03:19,560
I thought it was my fault.

1250
01:03:19,893 --> 01:03:22,351
That's why I wasn't
going to enter the Cup.

1251
01:03:24,225 --> 01:03:27,182
She bribed me to race.

1252
01:03:27,516 --> 01:03:30,098
Does this make
any sense to you?

1253
01:03:30,432 --> 01:03:31,265
Not really.

1254
01:03:31,598 --> 01:03:32,722
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

1255
01:03:32,972 --> 01:03:34,097
I forgot something.

1256
01:03:34,430 --> 01:03:37,387
So what did you do
when she hurt herself?

1257
01:03:37,637 --> 01:03:39,928
I helped her back, of course.

1258
01:03:40,261 --> 01:03:42,178
I mean, I'm not a jerk.

1259
01:03:42,469 --> 01:03:44,135
Aw, you helped her all
the way back to school.

1260
01:03:44,426 --> 01:03:46,342
Oh, that was nice.

1261
01:03:46,592 --> 01:03:49,591
I'm sure she really
appreciated that.

1262
01:03:49,924 --> 01:03:52,132
She usually pretty fast?

1263
01:03:52,382 --> 01:03:53,840
Yeah, she's good.

1264
01:03:54,132 --> 01:03:55,298
Faster than you.

1265
01:03:55,589 --> 01:03:56,881
At least that day.

1266
01:03:57,131 --> 01:03:58,213
Yeah.

1267
01:03:58,505 --> 01:04:00,046
Careful, that's hot.

1268
01:04:00,296 --> 01:04:03,753
How are you at losing?

1269
01:04:04,003 --> 01:04:06,169
I try to be a good sport,
you know,

1270
01:04:06,502 --> 01:04:09,210
but it makes me mad
when I lose.

1271
01:04:09,543 --> 01:04:11,917
[laughing]

1272
01:04:12,208 --> 01:04:15,166
I wonder where
he got that from.

1273
01:04:15,499 --> 01:04:16,456
Seems like somebody's
listening in

1274
01:04:16,706 --> 01:04:18,331
on our conversation.

1275
01:04:18,581 --> 01:04:21,746
You guys are so slow sometimes.

1276
01:04:23,330 --> 01:04:25,120
We do things at our own speed.

1277
01:04:25,370 --> 01:04:28,077
It's called man time.

1278
01:04:28,327 --> 01:04:30,743
I'm getting to it.

1279
01:04:31,076 --> 01:04:35,575
Look, I don't think it's
the race she's trying to win.

1280
01:04:37,324 --> 01:04:39,240
I think it's you.

1281
01:04:39,490 --> 01:04:42,323
She's always bothering me.

1282
01:04:44,364 --> 01:04:48,529
Look, you have to get
past the competition.

1283
01:04:48,778 --> 01:04:50,112
You have to see the person.

1284
01:04:50,445 --> 01:04:51,611
She's just a young girl.

1285
01:04:51,861 --> 01:04:53,652
She got all this stuff
going on inside of her.

1286
01:04:53,902 --> 01:04:57,692
She doesn't know how
to express it, right?

1287
01:04:59,691 --> 01:05:02,690
Is that what you're doing?

1288
01:05:02,940 --> 01:05:05,065
Seeing the person there?

1289
01:05:05,356 --> 01:05:07,564
What do you mean?

1290
01:05:07,855 --> 01:05:11,187
With Mitch.

1291
01:05:11,437 --> 01:05:12,937
You've been doing all this
